In this article, President Obama is interviewed by Mark Jones on ESPN 2. They discuss the first half of the basketball game, with the President noting that the Brazilian team is competitive due to the number of Brazilians in the NBA. He predicts that the second half will not be close. They also discuss the culture change in USA Basketball, with Coach Krzyzewski turning the team around after a disappointing performance in 2004. The President praises the talent on the team and their dedication to representing the United States well. They also touch on Kobe Bryant's comment that the current team would beat the 1992 Dream Team, with the President stating that he still believes the original Dream Team was the best. The interview concludes with the President discussing his experience coaching his daughters and a pickup game that took place at the White House for his 49th birthday.